<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-ED686C62-EE2A-4677-A9CC-53E6EBB34E5C" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-ED686C62-EE2A-4677-A9CC-53E6EBB34E5C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b translate="no" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> 490051: Printhead temperature result too low during Waveform calibration</b> </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-50151BE1-0690-4312-A8E6-CFE91A966199"><p class="- topic/p ">During waveform calibration the needed the temperature of the printheads is too low. The needed temperature is related to the viscosity of the ink.
</p></abstract><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-8835C729-E4AD-422B-A94C-96EF7C3CAB46" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Patterns in calibration print</u> 
</p><table id="GUID-EBCFE30A-C9C2-4DC8-AF34-1F4196B57C8E" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="6.08*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> C1640/C1650
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-36DC2450-80E7-421E-8A1A-836ED6647905" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-47EB3B36-C477-48AB-856E-AD8B9352605C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-47EB3B36-C477-48AB-856E-AD8B9352605C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> C1630/CMxx
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is generated during the calibration step "PrintheadWaveforms" which is part of one the following calibration sequences:
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Printhead calibration via the UI
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- SDS 04-6-026: “Execute printhead calibrations [Special Tests]”
</p></section><section id="GUID-26CDC561-3D31-4025-B6B4-F9780FA7BA04" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Analyse/Repair</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the expired ink from the system by following procedure "<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u "> 02 The (expired) ink replacement procedure including flushing tubes</u>" in the TSM. Afterwards redo the calibration.
</p></section><section id="GUID-0D913BEB-FF29-4E24-9F90-D2D80BECBBC5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Prevent ink to expire in the engine.
</p></section><section id="GUID-A0A7223B-F7C9-4445-902F-6ABD047F013A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">During waveform calibration the temperature of the printheads is adjusted to set the correct viscosity of the ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is needed to get a uniform droplet size. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When this setpoint is out of range the viscosity of the ink itself is not what it supposed to be.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F2864082-F34C-4657-B37E-EA7C5343FE90.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
